WEBVTT

00:04.175 --> 00:06.207
[♪ mid-tempo music]

00:08.109 --> 00:11.642
Six years ago, a 12-year-old
pop star with a Tennessee twang,

00:11.642 --> 00:15.286
exploded onto the music scene,
taking the world by storm.

00:15.286 --> 00:18.449
Since then,
Hannah Montana has dazzled us

00:18.449 --> 00:20.221
with her incredible talent,

00:20.221 --> 00:24.155
her infectious charm,
and her unique style.

00:24.155 --> 00:26.427
But underneath all that
amazing talent

00:26.427 --> 00:29.029
was a secret
even more amazing.

00:29.029 --> 00:32.363
That famous blonde hair
was really a wig,

00:32.363 --> 00:35.266
that hid a regular
teenage girl.

00:35.266 --> 00:38.639
While Hannah was doing sold out
tours and blockbuster movies,

00:38.639 --> 00:41.612
the girl under the wig
was going to school,

00:41.612 --> 00:45.276
and trying to fit in
like any other teenager.

00:45.276 --> 00:48.249
Well, days ago, that teenager
stunned the world

00:48.249 --> 00:51.722
by revealing the truth behind
the international phenomenon.

00:51.722 --> 00:55.656
I'm Robin Roberts and today
we sit down with Miley Stewart

00:55.656 --> 00:57.728
the remarkable young woman
who is,

00:57.728 --> 01:00.491
or rather was,
Hannah Montana.

01:00.491 --> 01:05.096
As she, for the first time,
shares her amazing journey.

01:05.096 --> 01:07.498
[♪ mid-tempo music]

01:07.498 --> 01:09.400
[Miley] Whoo!

01:09.400 --> 01:10.771
Here we go, everybody!

01:12.543 --> 01:13.544
♪ Come on ♪

01:13.544 --> 01:16.747
♪ You get the limo out front ♪

01:16.747 --> 01:21.812
♪ Oooh, hottest styles
every shoe, every color ♪

01:21.812 --> 01:25.686
♪ Yeah, when you're famous
it can be kind of fun ♪

01:25.686 --> 01:30.090
♪ It's really you but
no one ever discovers ♪

01:30.090 --> 01:34.195
♪ Who would have thought
that a girl like me ♪

01:34.195 --> 01:38.399
♪ Would double
as a superstar ♪

01:38.399 --> 01:40.100
♪ Whooo! ♪

01:40.100 --> 01:43.874
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

01:43.874 --> 01:45.836
♪ Chill it out
Take it slow ♪

01:45.836 --> 01:47.638
♪ Then you rock out the show ♪

01:47.638 --> 01:51.512
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

01:51.512 --> 01:54.415
♪ Mix it all together
and you know ♪

01:54.415 --> 01:57.248
♪ That it's the best
of both worlds ♪♪

02:03.694 --> 02:09.830
♪ This is the life,
hold on tight ♪

02:09.830 --> 02:13.464
♪ And this is the dream,
it's all I need ♪

02:13.464 --> 02:15.706
Wow, you were so young, Hannah.

02:15.706 --> 02:18.569
I mean, Miley. This is gonna
take some getting used to.

02:18.569 --> 02:22.142
Yeah, for me too. I think it was
six years and 47 weeks ago.

02:22.142 --> 02:25.716
So that would make you what,
11, 12 years old at the time?

02:25.716 --> 02:28.919
I was 12 because I had
just got my first retainer

02:28.919 --> 02:31.552
so you could hear it when I
sang, "This is the life."

02:31.552 --> 02:34.785
What did you like most
about being Hannah?

02:34.785 --> 02:37.488
In the beginning,
I almost felt uncomfortable

02:37.488 --> 02:39.730
without the wig on or without
the makeup on, thinking,

02:39.730 --> 02:43.334
"OK, maybe true,
nobody does care about me
unless I look that way."

02:43.334 --> 02:46.767
But I got so confident because
what I learned was,

02:46.767 --> 02:50.741
the wig is not what
people are drawn to.
They don't know it's a wig.

02:50.741 --> 02:53.744
That's not what they like.
They don't like the mystery
of it, they don't know.

02:53.744 --> 02:56.307
It's me, it's just with
a different hair color.

02:56.307 --> 02:59.580
So that's what you liked.
What did you dislike about
being Hannah?

02:59.580 --> 03:02.953
Sometimes it was kind of

03:02.953 --> 03:06.857
a downer when you went
from all the hype of being
Hannah Montana,

03:06.857 --> 03:08.619
and people screaming your name
and whatever,

03:08.619 --> 03:09.760
and then you do
take the wig off,

03:09.760 --> 03:11.762
and you take off the eyelashes
and all the makeup

03:11.762 --> 03:14.765
and you're like, "OK, this is
who I really am."

03:14.765 --> 03:17.928
You know, I don't have eyelashes
up to here and I will,

03:17.928 --> 03:19.970
you know, my skin
will be bad sometimes

03:19.970 --> 03:23.804
or my hair won't look
that great, but it's like,
that is a real person.

03:23.804 --> 03:25.806
And that's what,
at the end of the day,
people did love about Hannah

03:25.806 --> 03:27.808
is she was real,
because I was real.

03:27.808 --> 03:30.911
Most kids, when they
dream of being a rock star

03:30.911 --> 03:32.583
they can't wait to be famous,

03:32.583 --> 03:35.346
but you created Hannah Montana

03:35.346 --> 03:37.548
so she'd be the famous one

03:37.548 --> 03:39.490
and nobody would know
who you were.

03:39.490 --> 03:40.921
I mean, why'd you do that?

03:40.921 --> 03:43.554
I mostly did it because
I had a famous dad

03:43.554 --> 03:44.995
and I saw what he
went through.

03:44.995 --> 03:47.398
Country rocker, Robby Ray.

03:49.600 --> 03:52.933
♪ I want my money back ♪

03:52.933 --> 03:56.807
♪ My old Camaro
and my 8-track ♪♪

03:56.807 --> 03:59.410
I saw some of the stuff
that he had to deal with

03:59.410 --> 04:03.814
and I kinda made Hannah
so I could

04:03.814 --> 04:06.917
get away from that a little bit
and have more of a normal life.

04:06.917 --> 04:09.249
You talk about some of the
things that he had to deal with.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.422
I mean, what are you really
talking about here?

04:11.422 --> 04:14.955
Mostly, I think
he really wanted people

04:14.955 --> 04:18.659
that loved him
just because he was Robby Ray,

04:18.659 --> 04:20.930
not because of any other reason

04:20.930 --> 04:23.964
or because of his career and
that's what I wanted too.

04:23.964 --> 04:26.367
I just wanted friends that
really loved me for who I was.

04:26.367 --> 04:27.898
Now did you find those friends?

04:27.898 --> 04:29.570
I did.

04:29.570 --> 04:32.773
♪ You're a true friend ♪

04:35.406 --> 04:38.909
♪ You're here 'til the end ♪

04:38.909 --> 04:41.812
♪ You're a true friend ♪♪

04:43.984 --> 04:46.957
And they found out
you were Hannah along with
the rest of the world?

04:46.957 --> 04:50.561
No, I told them as soon as I
knew that I could count on them.

04:50.561 --> 04:51.562
How'd they take it?

04:54.795 --> 04:57.328
Hey, Lilly, I think things are
gonna be a whole lot better

04:57.328 --> 04:58.799
around here now that you know
our little secret.

05:01.532 --> 05:03.033
I'm Hannah Montana.

05:07.808 --> 05:09.410
Pretty well.

05:09.410 --> 05:13.043
Really, so it didn't put any
strain on your friendships?

05:13.043 --> 05:16.917
Well, you know,
maybe a few times or, a lot.

05:18.349 --> 05:19.720
How much time do we have?

05:20.951 --> 05:23.654
I get the best seat 'cause
I'm her best friend.

05:23.654 --> 05:25.426
You mean her greediest friend.

05:25.426 --> 05:27.858
Well, it's better than being
her dumbest friend.

05:27.858 --> 05:30.731
Will you two just
work it out?

05:31.902 --> 05:33.904
Oh, look at that.

05:33.904 --> 05:36.437
I knew you two couldn't
stay mad at each other.

05:36.437 --> 05:39.840
Oh yeah, we're closer
than ever.

05:39.840 --> 05:43.043
Thank you so much for this
incredible honor.

05:43.043 --> 05:44.915
Every time that I
hear True Friends

05:44.915 --> 05:47.678
it always makes me think

05:47.678 --> 05:50.681
about... about real...

05:50.681 --> 05:52.853
[mumbling]

05:52.853 --> 05:54.785
America's Top Talent
will be right back

05:54.785 --> 05:57.428
with our next contestant,
Oliver Oken.

06:05.095 --> 06:07.498
I was just thinking about this.
You know, you really benefited

06:07.498 --> 06:10.871
from being able to see
how Hannah was treated,

06:10.871 --> 06:12.403
"Ahhhh, the superstar."

06:12.403 --> 06:14.044
And then Miley Stewart.

06:14.044 --> 06:16.747
- Right.
- In school, trying to get along

06:16.747 --> 06:19.079
the best she can
like everybody else,

06:19.079 --> 06:22.453
so you had the benefit of
really knowing how that works.

06:22.453 --> 06:25.085
It was great at times
and then sometimes, it just,

06:25.085 --> 06:27.958
I think I was so lucky
to have Hannah Montana

06:27.958 --> 06:28.989
and then Miley Stewart

06:28.989 --> 06:32.793
because I got to see
people's true colors.

06:32.793 --> 06:34.965
Oh, hey, look everyone,

06:34.965 --> 06:37.127
it's a couple of
last page losers

06:37.127 --> 06:38.629
in their native habitat.

06:38.629 --> 06:44.104
So sad, still eating as if
they had a reason to live.

06:44.104 --> 06:45.135
Ohhh.

06:46.837 --> 06:47.878
[ringing]

06:49.139 --> 06:51.482
Hello.

06:51.482 --> 06:53.013
Hey, Amber,
it's Hannah Montana.

06:55.486 --> 06:57.117
The producers asked me
to call you to tell you

06:57.117 --> 06:59.690
that you are one
of the three lucky people

06:59.690 --> 07:01.692
performing with me
on Singing with the Stars.

07:02.122 --> 07:04.154
Ahhh!

07:04.154 --> 07:06.196
Oh, Rico.

07:06.196 --> 07:09.560
Hey, Bubble Brain,
how's it going?

07:09.560 --> 07:11.662
- Rico.
- I'm sorry, girls,

07:11.662 --> 07:15.466
I'm looking for someone with
a little more cha, cha, cha.

07:15.466 --> 07:17.167
Ten thousand dollars.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.611
- Is that?
- It couldn't be.

07:20.611 --> 07:21.812
Sweet niblets.

07:21.812 --> 07:24.114
Hiya, toots.
Wear something yummy.

07:24.114 --> 07:27.177
But no heels.
I don't wanna climb too high.

07:29.520 --> 07:31.952
- Sit down, Missy.
- No problem.

07:33.183 --> 07:34.725
Let me tell you two something.

07:35.986 --> 07:38.458
Society has rules.

07:38.458 --> 07:41.592
One of those rules is
if you miss registration,

07:41.592 --> 07:44.935
you cannot register again
until the second semester.

07:44.935 --> 07:47.467
The second.
The rules are for schnooks.

07:49.770 --> 07:53.003
It's such an honor
to have you as part of our
senior class, Miss Montana.

07:53.003 --> 07:56.476
- Please, call me Hannah.
- Hannah.

07:58.178 --> 08:00.551
But we got to see your
true colors too.

08:00.551 --> 08:03.013
You know, because
you stayed grounded.

08:03.013 --> 08:06.617
- Definitely.
- For the most part, with all
this going on in your life.

08:06.617 --> 08:08.959
Yeah, and there was times
where I wanted to, you know,

08:08.959 --> 08:11.692
of course, anybody would
want to stand up and say,

08:11.692 --> 08:13.594
"Well, I'm Hannah Montana,"
or, "I'm this or that,"

08:13.594 --> 08:16.066
and I need this special
treatment or whatever.

08:16.066 --> 08:19.229
Of course, when there's things
going on in life that you can't

08:19.229 --> 08:21.201
control otherwise unless
you have, you know,

08:21.201 --> 08:23.734
something up on someone
but I, of course,

08:23.734 --> 08:24.975
there were times where
I would think that,

08:24.975 --> 08:27.077
but nothing
was more important,

08:27.077 --> 08:29.940
no thing, no anything
was more important

08:29.940 --> 08:32.582
than my friends and
normalcy and my family.

08:32.582 --> 08:34.183
What about your older brother?

08:34.183 --> 08:36.246
Was he any help in dealing
with this double life?

08:36.246 --> 08:38.919
Well, as my daddy always says,

08:38.919 --> 08:41.251
"What doesn't kill you
just makes you stronger."

08:41.251 --> 08:44.193
The truth is,
Jackson and I are...

08:44.193 --> 08:47.257
Totally and completely
in love.

08:47.257 --> 08:49.129
[audience] Whoooo!

08:49.129 --> 08:51.762
- [Hannah] Oh, no.
- I love Hannah Montana!

08:53.564 --> 08:56.937
I love Hannah Montana!

08:56.937 --> 09:00.040
I love Hannah Montana!

09:02.112 --> 09:06.877
Again, really sorry about the
whole convertible top thing.

09:10.951 --> 09:12.152
Hi, everybody.

09:13.884 --> 09:16.186
You got a little something
in your teeth.

09:17.327 --> 09:20.560
Eww, it's a fly, eww.

09:20.560 --> 09:25.936
You come to me now in your time
of need and beg for help.

09:25.936 --> 09:29.169
But when have you ever extended
your hand in friendship?

09:29.169 --> 09:32.202
When have you ever given me
the respect of calling me...

09:32.202 --> 09:34.775
...Godbrother.

09:36.246 --> 09:39.680
You made me wait 20 minutes
so you could put on

09:39.680 --> 09:43.013
some stupid costume
and do a bad imitation.

09:43.013 --> 09:48.088
You hear that, Fluffy?
More disrespect.

09:48.088 --> 09:49.289
Fine.

09:50.761 --> 09:54.294
I need your plotting,
scheming, twisted mind...

09:56.697 --> 09:58.929
...Godbrother.

09:58.929 --> 10:01.371
This is so sweet.

10:01.371 --> 10:03.804
- You totally cheated.
- You totally cheated.

10:03.804 --> 10:06.276
- You always do that.
Why do you do that?
- [repeating]

10:06.276 --> 10:09.680
- [mumbling]
- [mumbling]

10:11.241 --> 10:12.242
You stop it!

10:12.242 --> 10:14.044
You fight like a girl.

10:14.044 --> 10:15.786
I am a girl.
What's your excuse?

10:15.786 --> 10:18.018
No, no, no, no, no!

10:19.289 --> 10:21.291
I'm not going to let you
tell her my secret.

10:21.291 --> 10:23.353
All right, fine.
I'll tell her my secret.

10:23.353 --> 10:25.395
I have a sister
who's Hannah Montana.

10:25.395 --> 10:28.058
She's a lot heavier
than she looks.

10:28.058 --> 10:30.861
- Lift some weights.
- Eat some lettuce.

10:31.932 --> 10:33.764
But, you know what?

10:33.764 --> 10:37.267
In the end, no matter how much
of a snotwagon he was...

10:37.267 --> 10:39.109
Am I allowed to say
snotwagon?

10:39.109 --> 10:42.743
I have an older brother,
so it's OK to say snotwagon.

10:42.743 --> 10:46.817
OK, well then, my snotwagon
always had my back.

10:46.817 --> 10:49.119
♪ One in a million ♪

10:49.119 --> 10:50.721
♪ Yeah ♪

10:51.982 --> 10:53.924
♪ One in a million ♪♪

10:55.786 --> 10:57.157
[audience chanting]

10:58.929 --> 11:00.260
- Stop pointing at the watch.
- Sorry.

11:02.262 --> 11:04.134
What about the rest
of your family,

11:04.134 --> 11:05.966
were they in on
the secret too?

11:05.966 --> 11:08.068
Yeah, they're my family,
I tell them everything

11:08.068 --> 11:10.741
but it's not
always the best idea.

11:10.741 --> 11:11.902
You know, actually,

11:11.902 --> 11:14.174
I never really thought
you were all that funny.

11:14.174 --> 11:17.247
Well, Elvis thought I had
a wonderful comic mind.

11:17.247 --> 11:20.310
Oh, I know what Elvis was
thinkin' about, and honey,

11:20.310 --> 11:22.412
trust me it had nothing
to do with your mind.

11:22.412 --> 11:25.255
- You take that back.
- You make me.

11:25.255 --> 11:29.119
And what makes this night
perfect is I can share it

11:29.119 --> 11:31.321
with the two women
who've inspired me

11:31.321 --> 11:35.125
with their character,
strength, and of course...

11:35.125 --> 11:37.397
- Man stealer!
- Sore loser!

11:39.129 --> 11:40.430
Ahhhh!

11:42.733 --> 11:45.175
- I'll be right back.
- [screaming]

11:49.880 --> 11:52.042
♪ Everybody makes mistakes ♪

11:55.415 --> 11:58.218
♪ Everybody has those days ♪

11:58.218 --> 12:00.450
♪ One, two, three, four ♪

12:00.450 --> 12:04.254
♪ Everybody makes mistakes
Everybody has those days ♪

12:04.254 --> 12:06.296
♪ Everybody knows what
What I'm talkin' 'bout ♪

12:06.296 --> 12:07.898
♪ Everybody gets that way ♪

12:07.898 --> 12:09.499
♪ Everybody makes mistakes ♪

12:09.499 --> 12:12.462
♪ Everybody has those days
Everybody...

12:15.135 --> 12:17.007
Uncle Earl!

12:18.168 --> 12:19.770
If you think
that was embarrassing,

12:19.770 --> 12:21.441
there was this
other time that Mamaw...

12:21.441 --> 12:24.144
Miley, remember when you asked
me how much time we have?

12:24.144 --> 12:25.345
Got it, movin' on.

12:25.345 --> 12:27.918
♪ La-dee-aah-aah-ooh ♪

12:30.921 --> 12:32.422
[♪ mid-tempo music]

12:34.454 --> 12:38.128
Being Hannah, obviously
complicated your life

12:38.128 --> 12:39.830
so it had to be relief
when you could just

12:39.830 --> 12:43.193
go back to being Miley
and that normal life
you talk about.

12:43.193 --> 12:46.036
Right, well the truth is,
that normal life

12:46.036 --> 12:48.869
didn't end up being as normal
as I thought it would be.

12:49.800 --> 12:52.042
You are one evil little boy.

12:52.042 --> 12:55.545
- Hit it.
- Whoa!

12:55.545 --> 12:57.908
[screaming]

12:57.908 --> 13:00.150
I wanna serve up some justice

13:00.150 --> 13:02.983
and I think I know just who
I wanna serve it up on.

13:03.914 --> 13:05.315
Oh, boy.

13:09.419 --> 13:10.560
Oliver, go deep.

13:28.138 --> 13:29.910
What do you think,
a little too much?

13:32.382 --> 13:36.046
And somewhere in all of this,
you found time to date?

13:36.046 --> 13:39.049
Now how exactly does that work,
living two lives?

13:39.049 --> 13:42.923
Well, that question's easy.
It doesn't work.

13:42.923 --> 13:45.395
♪ Nobody's perfect
I gotta work it ♪

13:45.395 --> 13:49.930
♪ Again and again
'Til I get it right ♪

13:49.930 --> 13:53.563
♪ Nobody's perfect
